# Force LF endings on the sync script. It carries a `#!/usr/bin/env python3` shebang, and a
# stray CRLF would make Linux/macOS fail to launch `./sync.py` ("bad interpreter: python3\r").
# Editing on Windows won't reintroduce CRLF because of this rule.
*.py text eol=lf

# Force LF on all Markdown too. The workflow `publish` engine writes settled prose into these
# docs and preserves whatever newline style it finds; pinning docs to LF keeps that stable across
# machines (Windows editors won't reintroduce CRLF) and closes RISKS #10 for docs.
*.md text eol=lf
